<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-11T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-11T05:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2178: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-11T18:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 11,
                                            1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        April 12, 10.22 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>My telegram of April 10th, 8 p.m.<note n="96" xml:id="d461fn96">Undoubtedly refers to undated telegram received April 10, 7.40
                                    p.m., <ref target="#pg_507">p. 507</ref>.</note> I am informed
                                that an answer from the Minister of Finance extending the currency
                                loan option for six months was sent to the chairman of the group
                                banks yesterday.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>